cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a new approach for facial image analysis using Active Appearance Model (AAM) fitting. AAM is a commonly used method in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision and pattern recognition. The paper specifically focuses on image alignment and proposes a bidirectional warping approach. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for image alignment, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves optimization techniques for AAM fitting, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves geometric transformations, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics).
